message: Welcome! Here's what I learned: 1. 'Scissors' on 'artificial, soft' items (like paper/cardboard) gives +25. 2. Applying 'frame' to these 'cut' items boosts them to +45. 3. The same 'scissors' then 'frame' combo works for 'natural, soft' items (like mushroom/leaf) for +45. 4. Combining a 'natural, hard' item (rock/pinecone) with an 'artificial, hard' item (buttons) gives +30. 5. Framing this 'hard' combination boosts it to +50! 6. WARNING: Do NOT use 'scissors' on 'hard' items (negative). 7. Also, combining *already framed* items, or applying tools to items with the 'ruined frame' feature, consistently creates highly negative values. Aim for 45-50 and submit.
